To post a message when the right mouse button is clicked, you can use the following code in JavaScript:

```javascript
document.addEventListener("contextmenu", function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();

  // Your message
  var message = "Right mouse button clicked.";

  // Post the message
  console.log(message); // or use any other method to display the message

});
```

Explanation:

1. The `addEventListener` method is used to listen for the `contextmenu` event, which is triggered when the right mouse button is clicked.

2. The `e.preventDefault()` method is used to prevent the default context menu from appearing (optional, depending on your requirement).

3. Inside the event listener, you can define the message you want to post when the right mouse button is clicked.

4. Finally, you can call any method (in this example, `console.log`) or perform any action to display or post the message.

To use `postMessage` to send a message when the right mouse button is clicked, you can use the following code:

