2. The `sendRightClickMessage` function is used to send the message to the child window or iframe. It uses the `postMessage` method to send the message string, along with the target origin set to `"*"` for any origin.

3. In the child window or iframe, another event listener is added to listen for the `message` event. When a message is received, it checks if it matches the message indicating that the right mouse button was clicked. If it matches, it handles the message accordingly (in this case, logging a message to the console).

Make sure to replace `"childWindow"` with the appropriate ID or reference to your child window or iframe element.

